               <head>Kulliyyat-i Sa'di</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Kullīyāt-i Saʿdī by Shaykh Saʿdī Shīrāzī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129656 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85103852 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064361" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4064-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alternative" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100104792010.0x000001 viaf_100206721">Shaykh Saʿdī Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100104792010.0x000001 viaf_100206721" type="alternative">شيخ سعدى شيرازى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20031">Kullīyāt-i Saʿdī</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20031">كلّيّات سعدى</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Large portion of a damaged manuscript, with several lacunae, displacements, and forged catchwords</p>
                        <p>Illuminated throughout in the Ṣafavid 'commercial' Shīrāz style</p>
                        <p>Consists of mulammaʿāt, tarjīʿāt, ṭayyibāt, badāʾiʿ (ghazalīyāt-i nau), muṭāyabāt, muz̤ḥikāt, majālis, rasāʾil, rubāʿīyāt, khavātīm, ghazalīyāt-i qadīm, al-ṣāḥibīyah, muqaṭṭaʿāt,
                mas̲navīyāt, qaṣāʾid, and marās̲ī</p>
                        <p>Not dated</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
